    body_id: `## Ringkasan

React dan Vue tetap menjadi dua framework frontend paling populer di 2024. Artikel ini memberikan perbandingan objektif untuk membantu Anda memilih framework yang tepat berdasarkan kebutuhan project, tim, dan skalabilitas.

## Key Points

- React memiliki ecosystem yang lebih besar dan community support
- Vue menawarkan learning curve yang lebih landai
- React lebih suitable untuk complex enterprise applications
- Vue excel di rapid prototyping dan small-to-medium projects
- Keduanya memiliki performance yang comparable di 2024
- TypeScript support excellent di kedua framework
- Job market favor React secara global

## Performance Comparison

### Bundle Size

**Vue 3:**
- Runtime: ~34kb gzipped
- Better tree-shaking
- Smaller initial payload

**React 18:**
- Runtime: ~42kb gzipped (dengan React DOM)
- Requires additional libraries untuk full functionality
- Larger ecosystem = larger potential bundles

### Runtime Performance

Kedua framework memiliki performance yang sangat similar di 2024:

- Virtual DOM optimization setara
- React Server Components memberikan edge untuk SSR
- Vue 3 Composition API competitive dengan React Hooks
- Hydration performance similar

## Developer Experience

### Learning Curve

**Vue:**
- Simpler API surface
- HTML-based templates lebih intuitive untuk beginners
- Single File Components (SFC) organized dan clear
- Gradual adoption possible

**React:**
- Steeper learning curve
- JSX requires mental shift
- Hooks paradigm butuh waktu untuk master
- More concepts to understand (state, props, context, effects)

### Tooling

**Vue:**
- Vue CLI / Vite (official)
- Vue Devtools excellent
- Single source of truth untuk ecosystem

**React:**
- Create React App / Vite / Next.js
- React Devtools mature
- Fragmented ecosystem (banyak choices)

## Ecosystem & Community

### Library Support

**React:**
- Larger ecosystem
- More third-party components
- Better enterprise adoption
- More job opportunities

**Vue:**
- Smaller but growing ecosystem
- Official libraries (Vue Router, Pinia/Vuex) well-maintained
- Strong in Asia (terutama China)
- Fewer job opportunities globally

### Community & Resources

**React:**
- Massive community
- Countless tutorials dan courses
- StackOverflow answers plentiful
- Regular conferences dan meetups

**Vue:**
- Passionate community
- Quality over quantity untuk resources
- Official documentation excellent
- Growing international presence

## Use Cases

### When to Choose React

- Large-scale enterprise applications
- Complex state management requirements
- Need for React Native (mobile)
- Team dengan JavaScript/TypeScript background kuat
- Long-term project dengan scaling needs
- Access to experienced React developers

### When to Choose Vue

- Rapid prototyping dan MVPs
- Small-to-medium sized applications
- Teams dengan mixed skill levels
- Migrating dari jQuery atau vanilla JS
- Projects requiring gradual adoption
- Limited budget untuk hiring/training

## Migration & Interoperability

### React

- Harder to integrate dengan existing projects
- All-in commitment biasanya required
- Micro-frontends possible dengan Module Federation
- Next.js provides full-stack solution

### Vue

- Progressive adoption strategy works well
- Can be used sebagai enhancement untuk existing pages
- Nuxt.js provides full-stack capabilities
- Easier to integrate dengan backend templates

## Cost Considerations

### Development Costs

**React:**
- Higher initial training costs
- More expensive developers (higher demand)
- Longer development time untuk beginners
- Better long-term scalability = lower maintenance

**Vue:**
- Lower training costs
- Developers generally less expensive
- Faster development untuk small projects
- May need refactoring untuk large-scale apps

### Hiring

**React:**
- Larger talent pool
- Higher salary expectations
- Easier to find senior developers
- More competitive hiring market

**Vue:**
- Smaller talent pool
- Lower average salaries
- Harder to find senior Vue developers
- Less competitive hiring

## Future Outlook

### React Roadmap

- Server Components becoming stable
- Concurrent Features maturing
- Better Suspense support
- Continued Meta backing

### Vue Roadmap

- Vue 3 fully adopted
- Composition API improvements
- Better TypeScript integration
- Strong community-driven development

## Kesimpulan

Tidak ada "winner" yang clear. Pilihan tergantung pada:

1. **Project requirements** - complexity, scale, timeline
2. **Team expertise** - existing skills, learning capacity
3. **Long-term goals** - maintenance, hiring, scaling
4. **Budget constraints** - development costs, hiring costs

**Recommendation:**
- Enterprise/complex apps → React
- Startups/MVPs → Vue
- Mobile needs → React (React Native)
- Quick time-to-market → Vue

Kedua framework excellent choices di 2024. Yang terpenting adalah consistency dan best practices dalam implementation.`,
