    excerpt_id: 'Making website accessible to everyone bukan hanya good practice, tapi essential.',
    excerpt_en: 'Making your website accessible to everyone is not just good practice, it\'s essential.',
    body_id: `## Ringkasan

Web accessibility memastikan websites dapat digunakan oleh semua people, termasuk those dengan disabilities. Ini adalah ethical responsibility, legal requirement, dan business imperative.

## Key Points

- 15% global population lives with some form of disability
- Accessibility improves experience untuk semua users
- Legal requirements increasing globally
- SEO benefits dari accessibility improvements
- Better code quality dan maintainability
- Larger addressable market
- Corporate social responsibility

## Understanding Disabilities

### Visual Impairments
- Blindness (screen reader users)
- Low vision (magnification needs)
- Color blindness

### Auditory Impairments
- Deafness
- Hard of hearing

### Motor/Mobility Impairments
- Limited fine motor control
- Paralysis
- Tremors

### Cognitive Impairments
- Learning disabilities
- Memory impairments
- Attention disorders
- Autism spectrum

## WCAG Guidelines

### Four Principles (POUR)

**Perceivable**
- Text alternatives for non-text content
- Captions for videos
- Content can be presented in different ways
- Sufficient color contrast

**Operable**
- Keyboard accessible
- Enough time to read dan use content
- No content that causes seizures
- Help users navigate dan find content

**Understandable**
- Text readable dan understandable
- Content appears dan operates predictably
- Help users avoid dan correct mistakes

**Robust**
- Maximize compatibility dengan assistive technologies
- Use valid, semantic HTML

### Compliance Levels

**Level A** - Minimum accessibility
**Level AA** - Addresses major barriers (target this)
**Level AAA** - Highest level (not always achievable)

## Common Accessibility Issues

### Images
❌ Missing alt text
✅ Descriptive alt text for informative images
✅ Empty alt="" for decorative images

### Links
❌ "Click here" link text
✅ Descriptive link text ("Read our accessibility guide")

### Forms
❌ Missing labels
✅ Associated labels for all inputs
✅ Clear error messages
✅ Instructions for complex fields

### Keyboard Navigation
❌ Mouse-only interactions
✅ Full keyboard accessibility
✅ Visible focus indicators
✅ Logical tab order

### Color
❌ Color alone conveys information
✅ Color plus text atau icons
✅ Sufficient contrast ratios (4.5:1 minimum)

### Videos
❌ No captions
✅ Closed captions
✅ Transcripts
✅ Audio descriptions when needed

### Headings
❌ Skipped heading levels
✅ Logical heading hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3)

## Technical Implementation

### Semantic HTML
\`\`\`html
<!-- Bad -->
<div class="button">Submit</div>

<!-- Good -->
<button type="submit">Submit</button>
\`\`\`

### ARIA Attributes
Use when semantic HTML not sufficient:
\`\`\`html
<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">
  Form submitted successfully!
</div>
\`\`\`

### Focus Management
\`\`\`css
/* Visible focus indicator */
button:focus {
  outline: 3px solid #005fcc;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
\`\`\`

### Skip Links
\`\`\`html
<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">
  Skip to main content
</a>
\`\`\`

## Testing Accessibility

### Automated Tools
- WAVE (Web Accessibility Evaluation Tool)
- axe DevTools
- Lighthouse accessibility audit
- Pa11y

### Manual Testing
- Keyboard-only navigation
- Screen reader testing (NVDA, VoiceOver, JAWS)
- Color contrast checkers
- Font size resizing

### User Testing
- Include people with disabilities
- Test dengan real assistive technologies
- Gather feedback pada pain points

## Business Case

### Legal Compliance
- ADA (Americans with Disabilities Act)
- AODA (Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act)
- EAA (European Accessibility Act)
- WCAG sebagai standard global

### Market Opportunity
- 1 billion+ people with disabilities globally
- $8 trillion in disposable income
- Aging population increases needs

### SEO Benefits
- Alt text helps image search
- Transcripts indexable
- Better structure = better crawling
- Lower bounce rates

### Brand Reputation
- Demonstrates social responsibility
- Positive PR opportunities
- Customer loyalty
- Competitive differentiation

## Accessibility Myths

### "It's too expensive"
Reality: Many fixes are simple. Building accessible from start costs little extra.

### "It makes sites ugly"
Reality: Accessible sites can be beautiful. Good design is accessible design.

### "We don't have disabled users"
Reality: You probably do. Many don't disclose disabilities.

### "It's too technical"
Reality: Basic accessibility is straightforward. Start with semantics.

## Quick Wins

1. Add alt text to images
2. Ensure keyboard navigation works
3. Fix color contrast issues
4. Add form labels
5. Use proper heading hierarchy
6. Add captions to videos
7. Test dengan screen reader
8. Create accessibility statement

## Accessibility Statement

Include pada website:
- Commitment to accessibility
- Conformance level (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Feedback mechanism
- Contact information
- Known limitations
- Enhancement plans

## Resources

### Guidelines
- WCAG 2.1: https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/
- W3C WAI: https://www.w3.org/WAI/

### Tools
- WebAIM: https://webaim.org/
- A11y Project: https://www.a11yproject.com/

### Training
- Udacity Web Accessibility
- LinkedIn Learning courses
- Deque University

## Kesimpulan

Web accessibility is not optional. It's ethical responsibility, legal requirement, dan business opportunity. Start today, make incremental improvements, dan commit to continuous progress.

**Action plan:**
1. Run accessibility audit
2. Fix critical issues first
3. Train team on accessibility
4. Include accessibility in definition of done
5. Test with real users
6. Create accessibility statement
7. Monitor dan improve continuously`,
